column9: The genetic evidence on the devsearch is showing 7.5 in the bubble on genetic tab, but the GCI scoring shows 8.5. The issue is the segregation. The genetic evidence tab is off by 1 point as it is not calculating the segregation points.

This is a recuration from one that was originally done on SOP v5.  It looks as though the new curator added new evidence and perhaps did not rescore all of the existing evidence.  It also looked like the curator misattributed the "predicted/proven null' label on variants that should not receive that label.  Will need to look into this further, but on the surface it looks like the website is correctly displaying what it has been given and what the curator intended.

This curation was transferred from HCM GCEP to HCVD AND recurated, scored and republished. It changed classifications from No Known disease relationship in HCM GCEP to Disputed in the H-CVD GCEP recuration, which means the GCI calculates the classification as NKDR but it is modified to disputed.

There are 9 probands but 7 variants because 2 variants are repeated among probands. The sheet here indicates only 5 variants. The genetic evidence tab is not adding the segregation points that are shown in the GCI.
No problems noted on this curation

The curation appears accurate in the GCI, all new scores for SOPv8 and greater, and the classifiction matrix shows all the right points, but the devsearch website does not show the appropriate 12 points for the genetics evidnce tab.

On quick look, this one looks fine to me (variants are accounted for on the dev site) - the only thing that is off is this is an example of an AR gene with probands with compound het variants - so the system is counting scores for EACH variant, not for the proband in total.  For example: one person with two LOF variants - system is counting 6 points instead of the 3 point cap.
